Class InboundMsgFilterHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.netty.channel.ChannelHandlerAdapter

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.netty.channel.ChannelHandler, io.netty.channel.ChannelInboundHandler, io.netty.channel.ChannelOutboundHandler

    public class InboundMsgFilterHandler
extends io.netty.channel.ChannelDuplexHandler
    Represent a Netty handler in charge of applying filters on the inbound Corfu messages in order to transform them. The transformation are supplied to this handler as a List of MsgHandlingFilters which will be applied in order. An example of such transforming filters is drop certain messages. Created by Sam Behnam on 5/18/18.
